                            <comment id="13290" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 19 May 2005 04:42:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for spotting this! That&apos;s a bug in MethodInvokingFactoryBean&apos;s getObjectType implementation: that method can be called without full initialization and should never throw an exception; instead, it should return null if it can&apos;t determine the type. I&apos;ve fixed it to return null if the method hasn&apos;t been prepared yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
